   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Build aDaycare Center for Children with Disability</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Children with severe disabilities are perceived to be a burden, as they require continual care which prevents caretakers from seeking employment and engaging in  meaningful activities. Katalemwa seeks to build a day care centre to support annually  50  children with severe disabilities like cerebral palsy, neurological and multiple conditions. This day care will retain these children as their Parents/caretakers go to work, at school or engage in other activities.</narrative>
  </description>
